# CODEOWNERS
#
# This file defines code ownership for automatic PR review assignment.
# When a PR is opened, GitHub automatically requests reviews from the owners.
#
# Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for everything in the repo
# This ensures no PR goes unreviewed
*       @REPO_OWNER

# GitHub configuration files
# Changes to workflows and templates require careful review
/.github/                       @REPO_OWNER
/.github/workflows/*.yml        @REPO_OWNER
/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/*.yml   @REPO_OWNER

# Scripts that power automation
# Must be reviewed for security and correctness
/scripts/*.sh                   @REPO_OWNER

# Knowledge base
# Requires review to ensure quality and relevance
/docs/knowledge/                @REPO_OWNER

# Critical configuration files
# Changes affect entire system behavior
/README.md                      @REPO_OWNER
/.markdownlint.json            @REPO_OWNER

# Note: Replace @REPO_OWNER with actual GitHub username during bootstrap
# Example: * @myusername
